&lt;p&gt;Percentage increase with comparison to Pranay&amp;#39;s score =&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\frac{38}{190}\times 100\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 20%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, Arav&amp;#39;s total marks is 20% more than the total marks of Pranay.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; option 4).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;<br><br><p><strong>ਦਿੱਤਾ ਗਿਆ </strong><span style="font-weight: bolder;">ਹੈ</span><strong>:</strong></p>

